      <h1 id="title">Mohandas Karamchand Gandhi</h1>
      <p class="side">-The Father of Indian Nation</p>
     
      <section id="tribute-info">
        <h3 id="headline"> Here's a time line of Mohandas Karamchand Gandhi</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>2 October, 1869</strong> Birth at Porbunder in Gujarat (Sudamapuri, Kathiawad)</li>
          <li>
            <strong>1876</strong> Beginning of Education at Rajkot
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>1883</strong> Married with Kasturba at Porbunder
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>6 July, 1891</strong> In India, introduced to Raychandbhai (Whom Gandhiji regarded as his Guru)
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>24 May, 1892</strong> Came to Bombay to start practice in the High Court as Barrister
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>22 August, 1894</strong> Founded Natal Indian Congress to fight colour prejudice
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>1903</strong> Founded Transvaal British India Association
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>25 May, 1915</strong> Founded Satyagraha Ashram at Kochrab, Ahemadabad
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>10 March, 1922</strong> Arrested. On 21 March sent to Yervada Jail. Remained in jail till March 1924.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>17 September, 1924</strong> Started 21 days fast for Hindu-Muslim unity
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>8 May, 1933</strong> Started 21 days fast for the improvement of Harijan's condition and was released at 6 p.m. from jail
          </li>
          <li><strong>3 March, 1939</strong> Started fast unto death at Rajkot and on settlement of the issue ended fast on 7 March, 1939</li>
          <li>
            <strong>8 March, 1942</strong> 	Addressed All India Congress Committee of Bombay and Quit India resolution was passed.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>18 January, 1948</strong> Broke fast by taking orange juice from Maulana Azad
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>20 January, 1948</strong> A bomb exploded in the midst of his prayer meeting at Birla House, Delhi.
          </li>
          <li><strong>30 January, 1948</strong> The day of martyrdom, was shot dead while on his way to evening prayer ground at Birla House (now Gandhi Smriti) by Nathuram Vinayak Godse.</li>
        </ul>
         <figure id="img-div">
        <img
          id="image"
          src="https://images.livemint.com/img/2019/09/20/600x338/35dfa2a6-dae0-11e9-8cad-8cb97eec827a_1568967394710_1568967428840.jpg"
          alt="Mahatma Gandhi"
        />
        <figcaption id="img-caption">
          Mohandas Karamchand Gandhi was an Indian lawyer, anti-colonial nationalist and political ethicist
        </figcaption>
      </figure>
          <p>
            "There’s not a single person in the world who is untouched by the teachings of Mahatma Gandhi — the father of our nation — the chief advocate of ahimsa and satyagraha."
          </p>
        <h3>Know more about Mohandas Karamchand Gandhi in<a id="tribute-link" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mahatma_Gandhi" target="_blank"> Wikipedia</a></h3>
        </h3>
